race.comment: Tough. BULLA VINAKA (5) draws wide but he missed a whisker in a CL1 at Canberra 11 days ago from the 10 gate. Keeps the 1.5kg claim and gets his chance in lesser company. ZEEMA (11) was heavily bet when winning a Braidwood Maiden by 7.7L. Has switched to the Frank Cleary yard and has more to offer. Will use the low barrier and don't underestimate. LIAMENA AVENUE (7) led and went close at Moruya two back in a 58 and that would have him in the finish. He flies this course/distance. BATTLE ABBEY (3) tumbles in grade off a 2L defeat at Moruya and a luckless run at Cowra. Carries a lot more weight, but he's placed 4/5 at the track over this distance and is up to this if he brings his A-game.
